11:
Hah. Rare for you to put your foot
down like this.
12:
But we don't have a choice. Trust in
the Diviners' Commission is at an
all-time low.
13:
I did foresee this coming to pass,
you know.
18:
But... What about living in peace and
harmony with the yokai?
21:
The people aren't interested in
visions of an idealistic future. They
want results.
23:
So we'll give them results. We'll show
them what fearsome yokai hunters
we can be!
28: But Chairman, you'll only lose out...
45:
Your sojourns in Starview are
working wonders.
47:
At this rate, you'll be in control of
your shikigami and out of the
Diviners' Commission by—
54:
I want to stay in the Commission...
With you!
60: It's the tengu boy! And his lackey!
62:
Filthy diviners... You can't pull the
wool over OUR eyes! You were the
ones who summoned the yokai in
the first place!
63:
You're working with the monsters!
You're one of them!
67:
How dare you speak that way about
the Chairman... You don't know
anything!
77: I hate you... I HATE YOU ALL!
79: But you don't deserve to suffer.
89:
Wouldn't you agree? It's the
complete opposite of your shoddy
disguise.
92:
Whoever you work for is crafty but
otherwise, a fool. As they say,
"Tactics without strategy is the noise
before defeat."
99:
Chairman... I'm sorry about what
happened this afternoon.
101:
They were saying such terrible
things... But I shouldn't have lost my
temper.
107:
Well. That's one thing we have in
common.
113:
Those people are foolish, yet have
no aspirations to self-improvement.
They refuse to admit their own follies
and weaknesses, yet fear for
themselves.
115:
They must remind you of the
villagers who offered you up as a
sacrifice.
117:
And yet... You feel it is only right to
protect them. Right?
124:
I'd always believed that the day you
were freed from the snake would be
the day you were freed from me...
126:
But it seems we're more similar than
I believed.
132:
Chairman, I don't think I can be like
Miss Stella or Princess Inaho.
134:
I'd agree, unfortunately. But you still
can learn much from them.
137:
If you wish to come with me on this
journey, you must grow both as a
person and as a warrior.
140: Yes, sir. I won't let you down!
